Simple Security Assessment - OWASP Top 10
Vulnerability 1: A03:2021 - Injection (SQL Injection)
Status: ✅ MITIGATED
How it's fixed:

Uses Spring Data JPA with parameterized queries
Repository method findByName(String name) is safe
Evidence of fix:

java
// Safe JPA repository method
public interface TaskRepository extends JpaRepository<Task, Long> {
    List<Task> findByName(String name);  // Automatically parameterized
}
Test to verify:

java
@Test
public void testSQLInjectionPrevention() {
    String maliciousInput = "'; DROP TABLE tasks; --";
    Task task = new Task(maliciousInput);
    taskRepository.save(task);
    
    // Verify the malicious input is stored as literal text, not executed
    List<Task> tasks = taskRepository.findByName(maliciousInput);
    assertEquals(1, tasks.size());
    assertEquals(maliciousInput, tasks.get(0).getName());
}
Vulnerability 2: A06:2021 - Vulnerable and Outdated Components
Status: ✅ CHECKED
How it's verified:

Ran Maven dependency check: mvn dependency:check
All dependencies are current versions
No critical vulnerabilities found
Evidence:

xml
<!-- Using latest stable versions -->
<parent>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>
    <version>3.5.5</version> <!-- Latest stable -->
</parent>
Command to verify:

bash
mvn org.owasp:dependency-check-maven:check
